title: SLYV's Holdings Could Mean 18% Gain Potential - Nasdaq.com
text: Looking at the underlying holdings of the ETFs in our coverage universe at ETF Channel , we have compared the trading price of each holding against the average analyst 12-month forward target price, and computed the weighted average implied analyst target price for the ETF itself. For the SPDR S&P 600 Small Cap Value ETF (Symbol: SLYV), we found that the implied analyst target price for the ETF based upon its underlying holdings is $68.81 per unit.
